00:25:53,130 --> 00:25:53,963
Yes.

555
00:25:53,963 --> 00:25:55,710
- What I need is a bulletproof vest.

556
00:25:55,710 --> 00:25:57,660
- A bulletproof vest?

557
00:25:57,660 --> 00:25:59,250
Is that what you want?

558
00:25:59,250 --> 00:26:00,660
A bulletproof vest?

559
00:26:00,660 --> 00:26:01,650
All right.

560
00:26:01,650 --> 00:26:06,330
I've got something just
as good right here.

561
00:26:06,330 --> 00:26:07,803
Have him back very soon.

562
00:26:08,790 --> 00:26:10,800
All right, here you are.

563
00:26:10,800 --> 00:26:12,993
This is for you.

564
00:26:14,190 --> 00:26:15,630
- A doll?

565
00:26:15,630 --> 00:26:18,903
- A royal knight in shining armor.

566
00:26:20,610 --> 00:26:22,950
And the coast is clear,

567
00:26:22,950 --> 00:26:24,123
so you better go home.

568
00:26:27,030 --> 00:26:29,670
Maybe both of you will learn something.

569
00:26:29,670 --> 00:26:30,930
- Both?

570
00:26:30,930 --> 00:26:34,023
- Well, there's you and there's him.

571
00:26:36,600 --> 00:26:37,650
- You're nuts, huh?

572
00:26:37,650 --> 00:26:40,800
- Well, the jury's still out. (chuckles)

573
00:26:40,800 --> 00:26:41,913
Take care, Billy.

574
00:26:42,960 --> 00:26:43,793
(bell jingles)

575
00:26:43,793 --> 00:26:45,029
Take care.

576
00:26:45,029 --> 00:26:46,515
(bell jingles)

577
00:26:46,515 --> 00:26:49,098
(gentle music)

578
00:26:57,822 --> 00:26:59,155
- Mom, I'm home!

579
00:27:00,429 --> 00:27:01,262
Mom?

580
00:27:07,140 --> 00:27:07,973
Mom?

581
00:27:07,973 --> 00:27:11,414
(gentle music continues)

582
00:27:13,278 --> 00:27:15,695
(door bangs)

583
00:27:25,050 --> 00:27:27,300
You know that girl at school today,

584
00:27:27,300 --> 00:27:29,730
she's kinda cute, huh?

585
00:27:29,730 --> 00:27:30,783
She doesn't like me.

586
00:27:32,430 --> 00:27:33,380
She's nice, though.

587
00:27:35,375 --> 00:27:36,510
Of course she's probably
nice to everybody.

588
00:27:36,510 --> 00:27:38,733
You know, she's one of those nice people.

589
00:27:42,210 --> 00:27:44,110
Nice people don't like people like me.

590
00:27:56,683 --> 00:28:00,908
I just wish this past
year just never happened.

591
00:28:00,908 --> 00:28:01,741
I mean,

592
00:28:03,930 --> 00:28:06,870
I just wish you could just stop time

593
00:28:06,870 --> 00:28:08,940
and live the good parts

594
00:28:08,940 --> 00:28:12,243
and fast forward through the bad parts.

595
00:28:15,270 --> 00:28:16,960
You, you,

596
00:28:16,960 --> 00:28:17,913
you don't know time.

597
00:28:17,913 --> 00:28:20,403
You just, you just sit
on the shelf all day.

598
00:28:21,240 --> 00:28:24,900
You're lucky you don't have
to worry about anything

599
00:28:24,900 --> 00:28:27,573
but looking good and being dusted.

600
00:28:31,800 --> 00:28:32,820
That's the life.

601
00:28:36,284 --> 00:28:39,201
(insects chirping)

602
00:28:40,484 --> 00:28:42,984
(dog barking)

603
00:28:53,663 --> 00:28:54,496
- Billy?

604
00:28:56,190 --> 00:28:57,366
Honey, what are you still doing up?

605
00:28:57,366 --> 00:28:58,830
Do you know what time it is?

606
00:28:58,830 --> 00:28:59,850
- Astronomy project.

607
00:28:59,850 --> 00:29:01,290
- Aye-yi-yi.

608
00:29:01,290 --> 00:29:02,640
Look at this.

609
00:29:02,640 --> 00:29:03,930
This is a mess.

610
00:29:03,930 --> 00:29:05,880
You have a homework on
your first day of school?

611
00:29:05,880 --> 00:29:07,650
No, it's not due till November.

612
00:29:07,650 --> 00:29:09,930
I just thought I'd get a headstart.

613
00:29:09,930 --> 00:29:10,880
- My kitchen knife.

614
00:29:13,740 --> 00:29:14,573
Right.

615
00:29:15,690 --> 00:29:16,523
Good boy.

616
00:29:18,540 --> 00:29:20,970
- I met some kids at school today.

617
00:29:20,970 --> 00:29:22,170
- God, I'm so exhausted.

618
00:29:22,170 --> 00:29:24,870
That was my third double
shift in four days,

619
00:29:24,870 --> 00:29:27,717
my feet are killing me. (sighs)

620
00:29:27,717 --> 00:29:28,717
I gotta take a bath.

621
00:29:31,050 --> 00:29:33,138
- Yeah, they really liked me.

622
00:29:33,138 --> 00:29:34,305
- What, honey?

623
00:29:35,573 --> 00:29:36,406
- Nothing.

624
00:29:40,206 --> 00:29:41,039
- Okay.

625
00:29:43,546 --> 00:29:44,963
- Goodnight.

626
00:29:44,963 --> 00:29:46,213
I love you too.

627
00:29:47,461 --> 00:29:50,264
(objects clattering)

628
00:29:50,264 --> 00:29:51,097
- Billy?

629
00:29:52,470 --> 00:29:53,303
Billy.

630
00:29:58,101 --> 00:30:00,684
(somber music)

631
00:30:26,554 --> 00:30:29,471
(mysterious music)

632
00:30:38,807 --> 00:30:40,662
- [Yarik] Ow. (groans)

633
00:30:40,662 --> 00:30:42,098
Blasted leg.

634
00:30:42,098 --> 00:30:44,266
Oh. (groaning)

635
00:30:44,266 --> 00:30:47,737
(suspenseful music)

636
00:30:47,737 --> 00:30:48,672
Look at this.

637
00:30:48,672 --> 00:30:52,944
It's a bloody catastrophe. (muttering)

638
00:30:52,944 --> 00:30:55,105
(suspenseful music)

639
00:30:55,105 --> 00:30:58,188
When I catch up to the rotten rascal.

640
00:30:59,443 --> 00:31:01,390
(knight groaning)

641
00:31:01,390 --> 00:31:03,004
Where are you, traitor?

642
00:31:03,004 --> 00:31:03,837
You can't escape,

643
00:31:03,837 --> 00:31:08,837
I'll pursue you to the
ends of the earth. (groans)

644
00:31:08,902 --> 00:31:12,050
(suspenseful music)

645
00:31:12,050 --> 00:31:13,440
Hi Jove,

646
00:31:13,440 --> 00:31:14,580
you're but a pup,

647
00:31:14,580 --> 00:31:16,710
hardly a squire of of
worth by anyone's measure.

648
00:31:16,710 --> 00:31:17,670
- What do you want?

649
00:31:17,670 --> 00:31:19,290
- What were you thinking, lad?

650
00:31:19,290 --> 00:31:20,670
Look at me leg?

651
00:31:20,670 --> 00:31:23,320
This is not gonna make an
impossible task any easier.

652
00:31:24,270 --> 00:31:26,640
Are you sure it is you who,

653
00:31:26,640 --> 00:31:27,926
who's needing me service?

654
00:31:27,926 --> 00:31:29,238
Oh, oh, oh.

655
00:31:29,238 --> 00:31:30,342
Oh!

656
00:31:30,342 --> 00:31:32,014
(armor clattering)

657
00:31:32,014 --> 00:31:33,300
(suspenseful music)

658
00:31:33,300 --> 00:31:34,428
- Mom!

659
00:31:34,428 --> 00:31:35,280
- Shh, shh, shh.

660
00:31:35,280 --> 00:31:36,113
- What do you want?

661
00:31:36,113 --> 00:31:37,143
- I, I believe, pup,

662
00:31:38,640 --> 00:31:40,380
that is for you to tell me.

663
00:31:40,380 --> 00:31:42,083
- Who are you?

664
00:31:42,083 --> 00:31:43,027
- I'm known as Yarik,

665
00:31:43,027 --> 00:31:45,390
knight of the Order of Fallon.

666
00:31:45,390 --> 00:31:49,488
And so it seems, by your
command, young squire,

667
00:31:49,488 --> 00:31:51,390
I'm again with an injury.

668
00:31:51,390 --> 00:31:54,870
It gives me the chills. (groaning)

669
00:31:54,870 --> 00:31:55,980
- Mom!

670
00:31:55,980 --> 00:31:57,330
- Why me, dear Lord?

671
00:31:57,330 --> 00:31:58,938
What can I make of this?

672
00:31:58,938 --> 00:31:59,948
- What's a better?

673
00:31:59,948 --> 00:32:00,900
What is it?

674
00:32:00,900 --> 00:32:02,340
- Right there, look!

675
00:32:02,340 --> 00:32:03,300
- She can't see me, lad.

676
00:32:03,300 --> 00:32:05,130
You're the only one who can see me.

677
00:32:05,130 --> 00:32:07,599
- Sweetie, you're dreaming.
- [Yarik] Oh, me leg.

678
00:32:07,599 --> 00:32:08,432
- Wake up.

679
00:32:08,432 --> 00:32:09,265
- I'm not dreaming!

680
00:32:09,265 --> 00:32:10,500
Right there, he's standing right there!

681
00:32:10,500 --> 00:32:11,940
- A bit tender.

682
00:32:11,940 --> 00:32:12,773
- Wake up, sweetie,

683
00:32:12,773 --> 00:32:14,040
you're still asleep.

684
00:32:14,040 --> 00:32:14,873
- Go away!

685
00:32:14,873 --> 00:32:16,590
- Haven't you caused enough
trouble for one night?

686
00:32:16,590 --> 00:32:17,640
- Billy, you're still sleeping.

687
00:32:17,640 --> 00:32:19,627
- Does it look like I'm sleeping to you?

688
00:32:19,627 --> 00:32:21,573
There's a man in armor
standing at the foot of my bed!

689
00:32:21,573 --> 00:32:23,730
- Stop bouncing around.

690
00:32:23,730 --> 00:32:25,320
I told you she can't see me.

691
00:32:25,320 --> 00:32:27,330
- [Mom] Billy, sit down.

692
00:32:27,330 --> 00:32:29,520
- You're the only one.

693
00:32:29,520 --> 00:32:30,353
- [Mom] Sit down!

694
00:32:30,353 --> 00:32:32,180
- Ah, let's, let's see what I got here

695
00:32:32,180 --> 00:32:33,453
on the old appendage.

696
00:32:34,421 --> 00:32:37,413
- Honey, you're dreaming.

697
00:32:38,796 --> 00:32:43,796
(armor squeaking)
(Yarik humming)

698
00:32:43,951 --> 00:32:45,240
You're all right now.

699
00:32:45,240 --> 00:32:46,073
- [Yarik] Very good.

700
00:32:46,073 --> 00:32:48,177
Here, there we go.
- Yeah, I'm fine.

701
00:32:49,993 --> 00:32:51,334
- Me leg's perfect.

702
00:32:51,334 --> 00:32:52,643
(armor clattering)

703
00:32:52,643 --> 00:32:55,140
- You see the reflection over there,

704
00:32:55,140 --> 00:32:56,730
from the fish tank?

705
00:32:56,730 --> 00:32:57,903
That's all it was.

706
00:32:59,490 --> 00:33:00,780
I'm gonna tuck you in.

707
00:33:00,780 --> 00:33:01,613
Come on.

708
00:33:03,060 --> 00:33:05,440
I know things have been tough on you

709
00:33:06,419 --> 00:33:09,447
'cause of your father and the move and on.

710
00:33:09,447 --> 00:33:10,560
You had a nightmare.

711
00:33:10,560 --> 00:33:12,330
I'm sorry.

712
00:33:12,330 --> 00:33:15,232
Honey, sleep tight and I'll
see you in the morning.

713
00:33:15,232 --> 00:33:16,065
- Okay.

714
00:33:17,045 --> 00:33:17,878
But...

715
00:33:19,902 --> 00:33:21,383
- You're all right now, aren't you?

716
00:33:22,950 --> 00:33:24,903
- Yeah, I'm fine.

717
00:33:24,903 --> 00:33:25,986
- Okay. Good.

718
00:33:27,322 --> 00:33:28,655
Good night, son.

719
00:33:29,636 --> 00:33:30,469
- Night.

720
00:33:32,880 --> 00:33:34,391
(Billy sighs)

721
00:33:34,391 --> 00:33:37,474
(suspenseful music)

722
00:33:38,790 --> 00:33:40,530
- That's enough of that, lad.

723
00:33:40,530 --> 00:33:43,180
No sense making all three
of us upset, now, is there?

724
00:33:45,230 --> 00:33:50,230
(Yarik groaning)
(armor squeaking)

725
00:33:51,150 --> 00:33:54,864
The leg won't seem to hold its place.

726
00:33:54,864 --> 00:33:57,720
Do you have something I
could tie it off with?

727
00:33:57,720 --> 00:33:58,770
A brace of some kind.

728
00:33:58,770 --> 00:33:59,603
Oh.

729
00:34:03,120 --> 00:34:04,410
- What do you want?

730
00:34:04,410 --> 00:34:06,120
- I told you before, lad,

731
00:34:06,120 --> 00:34:08,250
that is entirely your decision.

732
00:34:08,250 --> 00:34:12,093
I was summoned; at extreme
urgency, I might add;

733
00:34:12,960 --> 00:34:13,793
by you.

734
00:34:14,640 --> 00:34:15,480
- I did not.

735
00:34:15,480 --> 00:34:17,310
- I was more than surprised meself

736
00:34:17,310 --> 00:34:18,930
to be called at such an ungodly hour.

737
00:34:18,930 --> 00:34:22,440
But such as it is my duty
to serve, alas, here I am.

738
00:34:22,440 --> 00:34:24,570
Don't try me patience now.

739
00:34:24,570 --> 00:34:27,718
Let's see how this is going to work out.

740
00:34:27,718 --> 00:34:29,700
(armor squeaking)

741
00:34:29,700 --> 00:34:32,220
Oh, this won't work at all.

742
00:34:32,220 --> 00:34:33,690
- This is ridiculous.

743
00:34:33,690 --> 00:34:35,490
I'm going outta my mind.

744
00:34:35,490 --> 00:34:38,310
- Oh, I wouldn't laugh if I were you.

745
00:34:38,310 --> 00:34:39,780
It's all your fault after all.

746
00:34:39,780 --> 00:34:40,680
- My fault?

747
00:34:40,680 --> 00:34:42,692
- Well, who do you think
threw me against the wall?

748
00:34:42,692 --> 00:34:47,692
- What?

749
00:34:55,119 --> 00:34:58,202
(objects clattering)

750
00:35:13,710 --> 00:35:15,200
Where is that tin knight?

751
00:35:15,200 --> 00:35:18,930
- At this moment, he's
limping down the stairwell.

752
00:35:18,930 --> 00:35:21,930
- You expect me to believe
that you're the tin knight?

753
00:35:21,930 --> 00:35:24,240
- Actually, Bill, your belief
is a little consequence.

754
00:35:24,240 --> 00:35:25,830
I'm here until the task is completed,

755
00:35:25,830 --> 00:35:26,880
whether you like it or not.

756
00:35:26,880 --> 00:35:28,860
- What are you talking about?

757
00:35:28,860 --> 00:35:30,450
- I'm here to help you.

758
00:35:30,450 --> 00:35:31,283
- Help me?

759
00:35:33,660 --> 00:35:34,500
- Well, (chuckles)

760
00:35:34,500 --> 00:35:37,023
perhaps it's time to go
over a few of the basics.

761
00:35:39,060 --> 00:35:40,260
As a knight,

762
00:35:40,260 --> 00:35:42,480
as a knight of the Order of Fallon,

763
00:35:42,480 --> 00:35:44,220
I'm bound by honored to appear in service

764
00:35:44,220 --> 00:35:45,360
wherever the need is greatest

765
00:35:45,360 --> 00:35:47,558
and the subject is worthiest.

766
00:35:47,558 --> 00:35:48,480
- Worthiest?

767
00:35:48,480 --> 00:35:49,350
Me?

768
00:35:49,350 --> 00:35:50,970
- Your concerns mirror me own, lad,

769
00:35:50,970 --> 00:35:52,110
but that is the oath I swore

770
00:35:52,110 --> 00:35:53,520
and the life I choose.

771
00:35:53,520 --> 00:35:56,220
So I'm imagining that if you're
not the worthies of squires,

772
00:35:56,220 --> 00:35:58,530
your need must be especially great.

773
00:35:58,530 --> 00:36:00,210
- I don't need anything from you.

774
00:36:00,210 --> 00:36:01,881
- Oh, you don't?

775
00:36:01,881 --> 00:36:03,810
- Where do you come from anyway?

776
00:36:03,810 --> 00:36:06,360
- Well, without getting too technical,

777
00:36:06,360 --> 00:36:08,760
which I couldn't anyway, I'm simply,

778
00:36:08,760 --> 00:36:11,850
I'm from, I'm from there.

779
00:36:11,850 --> 00:36:13,980
You know? I'm from there.

780
00:36:13,980 --> 00:36:14,813
- Where?

781
00:36:15,843 --> 00:36:16,676
- Well there, you know?

782
00:36:16,676 --> 00:36:19,380
I mean, you can call it the other side,

783
00:36:19,380 --> 00:36:22,050
the magical plane, the other realm.

784
00:36:22,050 --> 00:36:23,790
But it all boils down to the same thing.

785
00:36:23,790 --> 00:36:24,990
I am stuck here.

786
00:36:24,990 --> 00:36:27,840
I can't get back there until
I assist you with your task.

787
00:36:27,840 --> 00:36:29,580
- [Billy] You're wasting your time.

788
00:36:29,580 --> 00:36:32,880
I don't need help from
you or from anybody.

789
00:36:32,880 --> 00:36:34,560
- Well, I wouldn't mind getting back

790
00:36:34,560 --> 00:36:37,320
just as quickly as I can.

791
00:36:37,320 --> 00:36:39,120
I have a lady waiting.

792
00:36:39,120 --> 00:36:40,343
- So just go.

793
00:36:40,343 --> 00:36:43,170
- I can't go until your
hour of need is past.

794
00:36:43,170 --> 00:36:45,090
So if you'll just think
of something quick,

795
00:36:45,090 --> 00:36:46,050
I'll be gone from here

796
00:36:46,050 --> 00:36:49,173
and back in the arms of
my beautiful ballerina.

797
00:36:50,820 --> 00:36:52,410
- Ballerina?

798
00:36:52,410 --> 00:36:53,280
- The fair Katrina.

799
00:36:53,280 --> 00:36:54,690
She's quite majestic, you know?

800
00:36:54,690 --> 00:36:57,573
And so light.

801
00:36:58,437 --> 00:37:02,460
Her hands, graceful beyond words, really,.

802
00:37:02,460 --> 00:37:03,293
You know, she's

803
00:37:04,957 --> 00:37:05,957
a ballerina.

804
00:37:07,580 --> 00:37:09,090
We were in the middle of a glorious dance

805
00:37:09,090 --> 00:37:10,143
when you called.

806
00:37:11,700 --> 00:37:14,250
- Well, it's all too overwhelming for me.

807
00:37:14,250 --> 00:37:15,900
I've got to sleep on it.

808
00:37:15,900 --> 00:37:18,000
- How can you sleep at a time like this?

809
00:37:18,000 --> 00:37:20,790
- I'm sure this is all just one big dream.

810
00:37:20,790 --> 00:37:23,133
- Let's, let's talk
about this now, shall we?

811
00:37:24,030 --> 00:37:25,770
- You're here to do what I say, right?

812
00:37:25,770 --> 00:37:27,570
- Well, more or less.

813
00:37:27,570 --> 00:37:28,980
- Good!

814
00:37:28,980 --> 00:37:32,310
Then let me go to sleep.

815
00:37:32,310 --> 00:37:33,660
- But what of the task,

816
00:37:33,660 --> 00:37:36,633
the adventure I was
summoned to assist you with?

817
00:37:38,070 --> 00:37:38,903
- Adventure?

818
00:37:40,061 --> 00:37:44,340
If I can get through school
tomorrow without being killed,

819
00:37:44,340 --> 00:37:45,790
it's adventure enough for me.

820
00:37:47,820 --> 00:37:48,720
I mean, you have to admit,

821
00:37:48,720 --> 00:37:51,960
this is just a pretty
hard story to swallow

822
00:37:51,960 --> 00:37:52,800
during the morning.

823
00:37:52,800 --> 00:37:56,073
So just let me get some sleep.

824
00:37:59,407 --> 00:38:02,157
(birds chirping)

825
00:38:05,730 --> 00:38:07,950
- Up and at 'em, boyo!

826
00:38:07,950 --> 00:38:09,480
