1091
00:48:55,320 --> 00:48:56,153
- Woo.

1092
00:48:57,330 --> 00:48:59,045
I thought I missed the bus.

1093
00:48:59,045 --> 00:48:59,982
- No.

1094
00:48:59,982 --> 00:49:02,508
(engine droning)

1095
00:49:02,508 --> 00:49:03,990
- Hi.
- Hey.

1096
00:49:03,990 --> 00:49:05,140
- You want some coffee?

1097
00:49:06,030 --> 00:49:07,290
- No.
- I don't wanna spill it

1098
00:49:07,290 --> 00:49:09,115
before I get on the bus.

1099
00:49:09,115 --> 00:49:12,327
Ah, where are my cigarettes.

1100
00:49:12,327 --> 00:49:13,377
You want a cigarette?

1101
00:49:14,370 --> 00:49:15,570
- No thanks.

1102
00:49:15,570 --> 00:49:17,220
- Mm.

1103
00:49:17,220 --> 00:49:18,053
Pickle?

1104
00:49:19,276 --> 00:49:20,553
Eh, high in salt.

1105
00:49:21,990 --> 00:49:23,220
It's the first time I've seen you smile

1106
00:49:23,220 --> 00:49:24,920
since you've started at the diner.

1107
00:49:26,520 --> 00:49:28,920
- I have a lot on my mind.

1108
00:49:28,920 --> 00:49:29,753
- Don't we all?

1109
00:49:31,680 --> 00:49:32,790
I know it's not easy,

1110
00:49:32,790 --> 00:49:35,760
a single mom raising a kid all on her own.

1111
00:49:35,760 --> 00:49:38,340
It's a small diner, people talk.

1112
00:49:38,340 --> 00:49:41,430
Besides, we're all in the same boat.

1113
00:49:41,430 --> 00:49:42,880
I mean, I have two of my own.

1114
00:49:44,970 --> 00:49:47,160
Listen, if you ever wanna talk, I'm here.

1115
00:49:47,160 --> 00:49:48,903
I don't gossip.

1116
00:49:55,380 --> 00:49:56,213
So what happened?

1117
00:49:56,213 --> 00:49:58,593
I mean, was he in bed with everybody?

1118
00:49:59,730 --> 00:50:01,230
What, was he sleeping around wit everybody

1119
00:50:01,230 --> 00:50:02,310
and then you throw him out?

1120
00:50:02,310 --> 00:50:03,410
Is that what happened?

1121
00:50:07,860 --> 00:50:08,943
Was he a wife beater?

1122
00:50:09,960 --> 00:50:10,793
Is that it?

1123
00:50:10,793 --> 00:50:11,626
He beat you?

1124
00:50:13,050 --> 00:50:14,090
I don't know what...

1125
00:50:14,940 --> 00:50:17,880
Why do we always love the
ones who hurt us the most?

1126
00:50:17,880 --> 00:50:18,713
I don't know.

1127
00:50:18,713 --> 00:50:19,546
Is it, is it women?

1128
00:50:19,546 --> 00:50:21,000
I mean, we love them,

1129
00:50:21,000 --> 00:50:21,900
we leave them.

1130
00:50:21,900 --> 00:50:23,583
We love them, we go back to them.

1131
00:50:25,170 --> 00:50:27,213
It's our own fault, I guess, it's women.

1132
00:50:29,357 --> 00:50:32,100
Well, at least I got you to smile.

1133
00:50:32,100 --> 00:50:33,200
You have a nice smile.

1134
00:50:35,358 --> 00:50:38,610
(pensive music)

1135
00:50:38,610 --> 00:50:40,210
- I'm just worried about my kid.

1136
00:50:46,735 --> 00:50:48,082
(suspenseful music)

1137
00:50:48,082 --> 00:50:49,440
- I got a bad feeling about this.

1138
00:50:49,440 --> 00:50:50,670
- What, are you chicken?

1139
00:50:50,670 --> 00:50:51,503
- No.

1140
00:50:52,710 --> 00:50:53,543
- Come on.

1141
00:50:53,543 --> 00:50:55,860
It's just a couple cans of spray paint.

1142
00:50:55,860 --> 00:50:57,653
Besides, who's gonna gonna miss 'em?

1143
00:50:58,560 --> 00:50:59,613
You're one of us now.

1144
00:51:00,930 --> 00:51:01,920
- Come on, Billy.

1145
00:51:01,920 --> 00:51:03,829
Time to earn that jacket.

1146
00:51:03,829 --> 00:51:06,746
(vehicles droning)

1147
00:51:21,055 --> 00:51:24,388
(door creeks and slams)

1148
00:51:27,150 --> 00:51:28,250
- Can I help you, son?

1149
00:51:30,579 --> 00:51:31,468
- No, no, sir.

1150
00:51:31,468 --> 00:51:32,301
No.

1151
00:51:32,301 --> 00:51:33,153
No, thank you.

1152
00:52:00,180 --> 00:52:02,040
- [Yarik] Isn't that jacket
just smashing, Billy?

1153
00:52:02,040 --> 00:52:03,903
They'll love it in juvenile hall.

1154
00:52:09,720 --> 00:52:10,980
If you really want to impress him,

1155
00:52:10,980 --> 00:52:12,845
why not take two?

1156
00:52:12,845 --> 00:52:13,980
Or three.

1157
00:52:13,980 --> 00:52:14,813
Or four.

1158
00:52:14,813 --> 00:52:16,080
Her, have another,

1159
00:52:16,080 --> 00:52:17,080
have another, Billy.

1160
00:52:17,970 --> 00:52:19,703
Look, why don't you take the whole lot?

1161
00:52:19,703 --> 00:52:22,517
That's, that's sure to impress the lad.

1162
00:52:24,045 --> 00:52:25,260
- Hey, what's going on here, huh?

1163
00:52:25,260 --> 00:52:26,793
What's going on, big guy?

1164
00:52:28,380 --> 00:52:30,870
- The, uh, dis, display fell over.

1165
00:52:30,870 --> 00:52:33,120
- Oh, the display fell over.

1166
00:52:33,120 --> 00:52:35,400
Well, you know, that
stuff happens sometimes.

1167
00:52:35,400 --> 00:52:37,887
Well, do you think you can put
these back where they were?

1168
00:52:37,887 --> 00:52:39,496
- Y, yes, sir.

1169
00:52:39,496 --> 00:52:42,346
- You think you can put 'em
back exactly where they were?

1170
00:52:43,470 --> 00:52:44,303
- Yes, yes, sir.

1171
00:52:44,303 --> 00:52:45,870
- How about you give it a try.

1172
00:52:45,870 --> 00:52:46,998
Go ahead.

1173
00:52:46,998 --> 00:52:49,831
(cans clattering)

1174
00:52:53,220 --> 00:52:54,360
- What's taking so long, man?

1175
00:52:54,360 --> 00:52:55,950
We thought you were caught.

1176
00:52:55,950 --> 00:52:58,313
- This is stupid. I'm not
going through with it.

1177
00:53:00,150 --> 00:53:01,816
- All right. Don't worry
about it, little buddy.

1178
00:53:01,816 --> 00:53:02,760
You'll get another chance.

1179
00:53:02,760 --> 00:53:04,060
Let's get outta here, man.

1180
00:53:11,760 --> 00:53:14,043
- Hey. (whistles)

1181
00:53:14,043 --> 00:53:15,570
You an artist, homes?

1182
00:53:15,570 --> 00:53:16,503
- No.
- No?

1183
00:53:18,507 --> 00:53:19,340
Then why do you need this, huh?

1184
00:53:21,120 --> 00:53:22,770
- Uh, I-
- Yeah.

1185
00:53:22,770 --> 00:53:23,603
- I, I didn't-
- You know what?

1186
00:53:23,603 --> 00:53:24,810
I've had enough of you guys.

1187
00:53:24,810 --> 00:53:25,890
Now you're gonna wait in the back with me

1188
00:53:25,890 --> 00:53:26,981
while I call your parents.

1189
00:53:26,981 --> 00:53:27,814
Let's go.

1190
00:53:27,814 --> 00:53:29,973
- Well, he did something
really bad, huh, Mom?

1191
00:53:31,728 --> 00:53:32,561
- Unreal.

1192
00:53:34,063 --> 00:53:35,733
Come here, don't stare.

1193
00:53:36,750 --> 00:53:37,770
You're right, that was bad.

1194
00:53:37,770 --> 00:53:40,540
You should never do something like that.

1195
00:53:40,540 --> 00:53:42,566
- What did you think was gonna happen?

1196
00:53:42,566 --> 00:53:44,583
What? I'm talking to you!

1197
00:53:44,583 --> 00:53:46,334
What were you even thinking of?

1198
00:53:46,334 --> 00:53:47,696
- Listen to me.

1199
00:53:47,696 --> 00:53:49,350
I said I didn't do it.

1200
00:53:49,350 --> 00:53:50,820
- I don't wanna talk about this anymore.

1201
00:53:50,820 --> 00:53:51,960
Go to your room.

1202
00:53:51,960 --> 00:53:52,793
- If Dad were here,

1203
00:53:52,793 --> 00:53:53,823
he'd understand.

1204
00:54:01,293 --> 00:54:04,043
(birds chirping)

1205
00:54:07,481 --> 00:54:10,148
(pensive music)

1206
00:54:51,750 --> 00:54:52,583
- Ah, come on, Billy.

1207
00:54:52,583 --> 00:54:54,330
It was a joke.

1208
00:54:54,330 --> 00:54:57,450
You know, Riordan's always
pulling the stunts like that.

1209
00:54:57,450 --> 00:54:59,750
- Yeah, it was like a
test of merit, you know?

1210
00:55:00,696 --> 00:55:02,013
- It wasn't very funny.

1211
00:55:03,270 --> 00:55:04,103
- Hey!

1212
00:55:04,972 --> 00:55:09,972
Get 'em!

1213
00:55:12,060 --> 00:55:12,990
- Billy, come on!

1214
00:55:12,990 --> 00:55:13,823
Hurry up!

1215
00:55:16,350 --> 00:55:18,090
- I've seen their kind before.

1216
00:55:18,090 --> 00:55:19,080
You stay in their company,

1217
00:55:19,080 --> 00:55:21,153
I predict nothing but bad times ahead.

1218
00:55:33,270 --> 00:55:35,400
- Well, you're in a gang.

1219
00:55:35,400 --> 00:55:36,783
- Are you a daft, boy?

1220
00:55:38,100 --> 00:55:38,933
- No.

1221
00:55:38,933 --> 00:55:42,150
I mean, the knight of Order of...

1222
00:55:42,150 --> 00:55:43,500
Well, something,

1223
00:55:43,500 --> 00:55:44,940
whatever you call it.

1224
00:55:44,940 --> 00:55:46,080
- Of Fallon.

1225
00:55:46,080 --> 00:55:48,090
And I'd hardly call it a gang.

1226
00:55:48,090 --> 00:55:49,950
- Well, what would you call it then?

1227
00:55:49,950 --> 00:55:53,370
A bunch of guys hanging
out in their castle?

1228
00:55:53,370 --> 00:55:55,140
You all wear the same clothes,

1229
00:55:55,140 --> 00:55:56,343
and you're all friends,

1230
00:55:57,180 --> 00:55:59,280
and you always have
somebody to watch your back.

1231
00:55:59,280 --> 00:56:00,630
- We're bound by honor,

1232
00:56:00,630 --> 00:56:01,650
a spirit of purpose,

1233
00:56:01,650 --> 00:56:03,450
a vow to help those in need,

1234
00:56:03,450 --> 00:56:05,433
not steal, terrorize and destroy.

1235
00:56:07,830 --> 00:56:09,120
If you wanna belong to something,

1236
00:56:09,120 --> 00:56:10,740
why not make it your own family?

1237
00:56:10,740 --> 00:56:12,180
- [Billy] I don't have a family.

1238
00:56:12,180 --> 00:56:13,800
- [Yarik] You have a mother who loves you.

1239
00:56:13,800 --> 00:56:14,633
- [Billy] Yeah.

1240
00:56:14,633 --> 00:56:16,320
Well, she sure does have
a funny way of showing it.

1241
00:56:16,320 --> 00:56:18,210
- [Yarik] You have a
lot to learn about love.

1242
00:56:18,210 --> 00:56:19,620
- Yeah, well, I don't do anything with her

1243
00:56:19,620 --> 00:56:21,815
and she doesn't do anything with me.

1244
00:56:21,815 --> 00:56:23,380
These are the only friends I have.

1245
00:56:23,380 --> 00:56:26,700
- Well, it seems to me you
don't have any real friends now,

1246
00:56:26,700 --> 00:56:27,600
but you certainly could.

1247
00:56:27,600 --> 00:56:29,100
You're a bright chap,

1248
00:56:29,100 --> 00:56:31,080
and sometimes bright good company

1249
00:56:31,080 --> 00:56:33,662
when you're not whining and
feeling sorry for yourself.

1250
00:56:33,662 --> 00:56:36,098
- [Dice] Help! Somebody!

1251
00:56:36,098 --> 00:56:37,745
- Do you hear that?

1252
00:56:37,745 --> 00:56:38,809
- What?

1253
00:56:38,809 --> 00:56:41,220
- [Dice] Help! (yelling faintly)

1254
00:56:41,220 --> 00:56:42,220
- Over here.

1255
00:56:43,286 --> 00:56:44,554
- [Dice] Help!

1256
00:56:44,554 --> 00:56:45,707
Help, I'm stuck!

1257
00:56:45,707 --> 00:56:46,800
- Do you hear that?

1258
00:56:46,800 --> 00:56:48,465
You hear that, lad?

1259
00:56:48,465 --> 00:56:49,298
- What?

1260
00:56:49,298 --> 00:56:50,131
- [Yarik]] Come here, lad.

1261
00:56:50,131 --> 00:56:53,460
Quickly.
- [Dice] Please, somebody!

1262
00:56:53,460 --> 00:56:54,690
- [Yarik] Look. See?

1263
00:56:54,690 --> 00:56:56,310
Down there, down there.

1264
00:56:56,310 --> 00:56:57,143
You see him?

1265
00:56:57,143 --> 00:57:00,774
- Help me, please!
- He's in trouble.

1266
00:57:00,774 --> 00:57:01,834
Hello?

1267
00:57:01,834 --> 00:57:03,417
- Ace, is that you?

1268
00:57:04,440 --> 00:57:05,940
- Let's get some help.

1269
00:57:05,940 --> 00:57:08,298
- I'm afraid there's no time, Billy.

1270
00:57:08,298 --> 00:57:09,360
- [Ace] Hey!

1271
00:57:09,360 --> 00:57:10,210
- We can do this.

1272
00:57:11,460 --> 00:57:12,690
- Are you nuts?

1273
00:57:12,690 --> 00:57:14,040
I'm not going down there for a kid

1274
00:57:14,040 --> 00:57:15,480
that would just as soon kill me.

1275
00:57:15,480 --> 00:57:17,040
- Billy, there's no time to get help.

1276
00:57:17,040 --> 00:57:18,450
That boy's life is in your hands.

1277
00:57:18,450 --> 00:57:19,583
It's all up to you.

1278
00:57:19,583 --> 00:57:20,947
- [Dice] Help!

1279
00:57:20,947 --> 00:57:22,364
Somebody, please!

1280
00:57:23,998 --> 00:57:24,949
Ace!

1281
00:57:24,949 --> 00:57:26,949
Somebody please help me!

1282
00:57:28,261 --> 00:57:29,212
Somebody!
- Hang on, man,

1283
00:57:29,212 --> 00:57:30,327
I'm coming.

1284
00:57:30,327 --> 00:57:31,818
- [Dice] Hurry, man! Hurry!

1285
00:57:31,818 --> 00:57:34,818
(suspenseful music)

1286
00:57:40,972 --> 00:57:42,722
Please, I'm slipping.

1287
00:57:43,661 --> 00:57:44,494
- Yarik?

1288
00:57:44,494 --> 00:57:45,327
- What is it, lad?

1289
00:57:45,327 --> 00:57:46,620
- How's that leg feeling?

1290
00:57:46,620 --> 00:57:47,978
- Oh, it's getting better by the minute.

1291
00:57:47,978 --> 00:57:49,490
Keep at it, lad.

1292
00:57:49,490 --> 00:57:50,406
(Dice yelling faintly)

1293
00:57:50,406 --> 00:57:52,280
- [Dice] Come on!

1294
00:57:52,280 --> 00:57:54,814
(suspenseful music continues)

1295
00:57:54,814 --> 00:57:56,425
Hurry up!

1296
00:57:56,425 --> 00:57:57,573
Help me out!

1297
00:57:57,573 --> 00:57:59,710
(suspenseful music continues)

1298
00:57:59,710 --> 00:58:01,543
I can't get my leg up!

1299
00:58:02,851 --> 00:58:05,637
(Dice yelling faintly)

1300
00:58:05,637 --> 00:58:09,470
(suspenseful music continues)

1301
00:58:11,446 --> 00:58:14,779
(Dice yelling faintly)

1302
00:58:18,501 --> 00:58:19,532
My arm is weak.

1303
00:58:19,532 --> 00:58:20,365
Grab this arm.

1304
00:58:20,365 --> 00:58:23,069
Grab this part right here.

1305
00:58:23,069 --> 00:58:24,417
(Dice speaking faintly)

1306
00:58:24,417 --> 00:58:26,221
- [Billy] I got you. Swing it up.

1307
00:58:26,221 --> 00:58:29,797
- [Dice] Grab, grab it. (straining)

1308
00:58:29,797 --> 00:58:30,630
Grab it.

1309
00:58:31,729 --> 00:58:33,238
Come on.
- Okay. Uh, uh...

1310
00:58:33,238 --> 00:58:34,410
- Come on, man.

1311
00:58:34,410 --> 00:58:35,533
Do something.

1312
00:58:35,533 --> 00:58:36,366
- All right, see this?

1313
00:58:36,366 --> 00:58:37,199
See this?

1314
00:58:37,199 --> 00:58:38,032
This is the controller.

1315
00:58:38,032 --> 00:58:39,549
We're gonna go up. Can you hang on?

1316
00:58:39,549 --> 00:58:41,051
- I'm just trying to hold on.
- Okay. We're going up.

1317
00:58:41,051 --> 00:58:42,180
Here we go.
- Get us outta here, man.

1318
00:58:42,180 --> 00:58:43,286
(motor whirring)

1319
00:58:43,286 --> 00:58:45,027
(motor clanks)

1320
00:58:45,027 --> 00:58:46,893
Oh, man, what's wrong?

1321
00:58:46,893 --> 00:58:49,445
(suspenseful music)

1322
00:58:49,445 --> 00:58:50,278
- Okay.

1323
00:58:50,278 --> 00:58:52,437
- [Dice] Man, you gotta do something.

1324
00:58:52,437 --> 00:58:54,000
- Now what, dragon slayer?

1325
00:58:54,000 --> 00:58:54,833
We're stuck!

1326
00:58:54,833 --> 00:58:56,164
- [Dice] Who are you calling to?

1327
00:58:56,164 --> 00:58:58,384
- Uh, it's, it's my guard angel.

1328
00:58:58,384 --> 00:58:59,460
Just, just, don't worry about it, okay?

1329
00:58:59,460 --> 00:59:00,930
- Guardian angel?

1330
00:59:00,930 --> 00:59:02,770
That's fine with me.

1331
00:59:02,770 --> 00:59:05,103
- [Yarik] If you can't
climb up, climb down.

1332
00:59:06,120 --> 00:59:09,390
- If we can't climb up, let's climb down.

1333
00:59:09,390 --> 00:59:10,950
You can do that, can't you?

1334
00:59:10,950 --> 00:59:12,810
- [Dice] Yeah, I can do that.

1335
00:59:12,810 --> 00:59:14,733
- [Billy] You can do it.

1336
00:59:14,733 --> 00:59:15,944
I'll go first.

1337
00:59:15,944 --> 00:59:17,550
(suspenseful music)

1338
00:59:17,550 --> 00:59:19,200
You know, you can follow me.

1339
00:59:20,790 --> 00:59:21,887
Don't be afraid.

1340
00:59:23,166 --> 00:59:25,020
You can do it.

1341
00:59:25,020 --> 00:59:25,890
Okay?

1342
00:59:25,890 --> 00:59:27,420
If you need support,

1343
00:59:27,420 --> 00:59:28,563
then use my shoulders.

1344
00:59:30,270 --> 00:59:31,290
And don't look down.

1345
00:59:31,290 --> 00:59:32,400
- All right.

1346
00:59:32,400 --> 00:59:33,900
Hey, man.

1347
00:59:33,900 --> 00:59:35,040
- What? Ow.

1348
00:59:35,040 --> 00:59:38,070
- With our colors and all,
you could have just...

1349
00:59:38,070 --> 00:59:39,240
Hey, thanks.

1350
00:59:39,240 --> 00:59:40,680
Be careful.

1351
00:59:40,680 --> 00:59:42,076
- You too.

1352
00:59:42,076 --> 00:59:44,661
(suspenseful music)

1353
00:59:44,661 --> 00:59:47,640
(Dice straining)

1354
00:59:47,640 --> 00:59:49,005
Okay.

1355
